snippet.textDisplay:
//Meaning:

The poet is enchanted by the intoxicating looks of a beautiful woman. Her simple ways are so charming that, the Poet is completely awestruck. 
He confesses to having fallen for her charms- hook, line, and sinker. The pull in her eyes can't let him stay away from her. He longs to take a passionate journey through her mystical eyes and can't bear the pain of separation...for he is hopelessly in love.// Beautiful!

It's been four years since I first heard this song. For very obvious reasons, I keep coming back to this song every now and then. Every time I hear this, it reminds me of the simpler times four years earlier, and the peace I felt when I first heard it.
